# Experiment No. 1

# Title

Design any database with at least two entities and relationships between them. Draw suitable ER/EER diagram for the system.

---

# Aim

To design a database containing at least two entities with relationships between them and to draw a suitable ER diagram for the system.

---

# Theory

A database is an organized collection of related data used to store, manage, and retrieve information efficiently.
Before creating a database, it is important to design its structure properly. Database design helps in reducing redundancy and improving data consistency.

An **ER (Entity Relationship) Diagram** is a graphical representation of entities, attributes, and relationships in a database system.

---

# Important Terms

## 1. Entity

An entity is a real-world object about which data is stored.

### Examples

* Student
* Course
* Employee

---

## 2. Attribute

Attributes are properties of an entity.

### Example

For Student entity:

* RollNo
* Name
* City

---

## 3. Relationship

A relationship shows association between entities.

### Example

* Student enrolls in Course

---

## 4. Primary Key

A primary key uniquely identifies each record in a table.

### Example

* Student_ID
* Course_ID

---

## 5. Foreign Key

A foreign key creates relationship between two tables.

---

# Problem Statement

Design a **College Database System** with two entities:

1. Student
2. Course

Relationship:

* A student enrolls in a course.

---

# Entities and Attributes

## Student Entity

| Attribute    | Description       |
| ------------ | ----------------- |
| Student_ID   | Unique student ID |
| Student_Name | Name of student   |
| City         | Student city      |

---

## Course Entity

| Attribute   | Description      |
| ----------- | ---------------- |
| Course_ID   | Unique course ID |
| Course_Name | Name of course   |
| Fees        | Course fees      |

---

# Relationship

| Relationship | Description               |
| ------------ | ------------------------- |
| Enrolls      | Student enrolls in course |

---

# ER Diagram Representation

```text
+----------------+         Enrolls         +----------------+
|    STUDENT     |------------------------>|     COURSE     |
+----------------+                         +----------------+
| Student_ID(PK) |                         | Course_ID(PK)  |
| Student_Name   |                         | Course_Name    |
| City           |                         | Fees           |
+----------------+                         +----------------+
```

---

# Table Structure

## Student Table

| Column Name  | Data Type |
| ------------ | --------- |
| Student_ID   | NUMBER    |
| Student_Name | VARCHAR2  |
| City         | VARCHAR2  |

---

## Course Table

| Column Name | Data Type |
| ----------- | --------- |
| Course_ID   | NUMBER    |
| Course_Name | VARCHAR2  |
| Fees        | NUMBER    |

---

# SQL Syntax

## Create Student Table

```sql id="6gzrti"
CREATE TABLE Student(
 Student_ID NUMBER(5),
 Student_Name VARCHAR2(20),
 City VARCHAR2(20)
);
```

---

## Create Course Table

```sql id="e4t0vk"
CREATE TABLE Course(
 Course_ID NUMBER(5),
 Course_Name VARCHAR2(20),
 Fees NUMBER(8)
);
```

---

